---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Rhythm | zomeren.studio"
  description="Four dimensions of rhythm, one principle: pattern, repetition, tension and release."
  lang="en"
  enPath="/rythm/"
  nlPath="/nl/rythm/"
  schema={`{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"WebPage","name":"Rhythm | zomeren.studio","description":"Four dimensions of rhythm, one principle: pattern, repetition, tension and release.","url":"https://zomeren.studio/rythm/","inLanguage":"en-US","isPartOf":{"@type":"WebSite","name":"zomeren.studio","url":"https://zomeren.studio/"}}`}
>
  <Header enHref="/rythm/" nlHref="/nl/rythm/" lang="en" />
  <main class="px-6 pb-24 pt-20 md:px-12 md:pb-36 md:pt-24">
    <section data-reveal class="py-10 md:py-16">
      <h1 class="fade-in-stagger m-0 text-[clamp(2.4rem,5vw,7rem)] leading-[1.08] tracking-[-0.022em]">
        Four dimensions of rhythm, one principle: pattern, repetition, tension, and release.
      </h1>
    </section>

    <section data-reveal class="py-10 md:py-14">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-8 lg:grid-cols-12">
        <div class="col-span-4 lg:col-span-3">
          <img src="/assets/images/rythm/earth.webp" alt="Rhythm visual" class="aspect-[2/3] w-full object-cover" loading="eager" decoding="async" />
        </div>

        <div class="hidden lg:block lg:col-span-3"></div>

        <div class="col-span-4 lg:col-span-6">
          <p class="text-[clamp(1.4rem,2vw,2.7rem)] leading-[1.24] tracking-[-0.012em]">
            Rhythm is more than movement. Rhythm is structure in time and space. It is a universal principle we find in
            the sun, the moon, the seasons, and the year. It is the same force that lets music breathe and design speak.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section data-reveal class="py-8 md:py-12">
      <div class="space-y-12 md:space-y-16">
        <article class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-8 border-b border-black/40 dark:border-white/40 pb-10 md:pb-12 lg:grid-cols-12">
          <div class="col-span-1 lg:col-span-2">
            <img src="/assets/svg/sun.svg" alt="Sun" class="human-element-icon h-[clamp(5rem,10vw,20rem)] w-auto max-h-[20rem] max-w-[20rem] object-contain" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          </div>
          <div class="col-span-3 lg:col-span-8">
            <h2 class="text-[clamp(2.2rem,3.7vw,5rem)] leading-none tracking-[-0.02em]">Daily pulse</h2>
            <div class="mt-3">
              <span class="inline-flex rounded-full border border-black/55 px-6 py-2 text-[clamp(0.9rem,1.05vw,1.2rem)] leading-none tracking-[-0.01em] dark:border-white/55">Sun</span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-4 text-[clamp(1.05rem,1.3vw,1.9rem)] leading-[1.3] tracking-[-0.01em] text-black/92 dark:text-white/92">
              The sun gives us day and night. This rhythm of light and darkness affects sleep, alertness, and hormone
              production. In music, this is the foundation: tempo and beat. In design, this is the grid that shapes
              visual flow. Solar rhythm structures experience through repetition and predictability, without becoming rigid.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-8 border-b border-black/40 dark:border-white/40 pb-10 md:pb-12 lg:grid-cols-12">
          <div class="col-span-1 lg:col-span-2">
            <img src="/assets/svg/moon.svg" alt="Moon" class="human-element-icon h-[clamp(5rem,10vw,20rem)] w-auto max-h-[20rem] max-w-[20rem] object-contain" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          </div>
          <div class="col-span-3 lg:col-span-8">
            <h2 class="text-[clamp(2.2rem,3.7vw,5rem)] leading-none tracking-[-0.02em]">Cycles of feeling</h2>
            <div class="mt-3">
              <span class="inline-flex rounded-full border border-black/55 px-6 py-2 text-[clamp(0.9rem,1.05vw,1.2rem)] leading-none tracking-[-0.01em] dark:border-white/55">Moon</span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-4 text-[clamp(1.05rem,1.3vw,1.9rem)] leading-[1.3] tracking-[-0.01em] text-black/92 dark:text-white/92">
              The moon works more subtly. Monthly cycles influence hormones, mood, and perception. In music, this
              appears as dynamics and nuance: crescendos, breaths, and modulation. In design, it appears in rhythmic
              patterns, intervals, whitespace, and breathing room between elements. Lunar rhythm brings the emotional
              layer, the flowing and connective quality.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-8 border-b border-black/40 dark:border-white/40 pb-10 md:pb-12 lg:grid-cols-12">
          <div class="col-span-1 lg:col-span-2">
            <img src="/assets/svg/seasons.svg" alt="Seasons" class="human-element-icon h-[clamp(5rem,10vw,20rem)] w-auto max-h-[20rem] max-w-[20rem] object-contain" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          </div>
          <div class="col-span-3 lg:col-span-8">
            <h2 class="text-[clamp(2.2rem,3.7vw,5rem)] leading-none tracking-[-0.02em]">Rhythm of change</h2>
            <div class="mt-3">
              <span class="inline-flex rounded-full border border-black/55 px-6 py-2 text-[clamp(0.9rem,1.05vw,1.2rem)] leading-none tracking-[-0.01em] dark:border-white/55">Seasons</span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-4 text-[clamp(1.05rem,1.3vw,1.9rem)] leading-[1.3] tracking-[-0.01em] text-black/92 dark:text-white/92">
              Seasons bring transition. The body adapts through temperature, energy, nutrition, and activity. In music:
              changing themes, sections, and tension arcs. In design: hierarchy, contrast, and progression of elements.
              Seasonal rhythm introduces variation, contrast, and direction within a larger pattern.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-8 border-b border-black/40 dark:border-white/40 pb-10 md:pb-12 lg:grid-cols-12">
          <div class="col-span-1 lg:col-span-2">
            <img src="/assets/svg/year.svg" alt="Year" class="human-element-icon h-[clamp(5rem,10vw,20rem)] w-auto max-h-[20rem] max-w-[20rem] object-contain" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          </div>
          <div class="col-span-3 lg:col-span-8">
            <h2 class="text-[clamp(2.2rem,3.7vw,5rem)] leading-none tracking-[-0.02em]">Macrostructure</h2>
            <div class="mt-3">
              <span class="inline-flex rounded-full border border-black/55 px-6 py-2 text-[clamp(0.9rem,1.05vw,1.2rem)] leading-none tracking-[-0.01em] dark:border-white/55">Year</span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-4 text-[clamp(1.05rem,1.3vw,1.9rem)] leading-[1.3] tracking-[-0.01em] text-black/92 dark:text-white/92">
              The year provides cyclical context. Long-term planning, projects, and creative processes follow this wider
              cadence. In music: arrangement over minutes or hours, build-up and resolution. In design: composition,
              balance, and structure across a page or interface. Year rhythm integrates all smaller rhythms into one coherent whole.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section data-reveal class="py-10 md:py-14">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-8 lg:grid-cols-12">
        <div class="col-span-4 lg:col-span-3">
          <img src="/assets/images/rythm/moon.webp" alt="Rhythm interplay visual" class="aspect-[2/3] w-full object-cover" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
        </div>

        <div class="hidden lg:block lg:col-span-3"></div>

        <div class="col-span-4 lg:col-span-6">
          <h2 class="text-[clamp(2.2rem,3.7vw,5rem)] leading-none tracking-[-0.02em]">Rhythm in people and creation</h2>
          <div class="mt-8 space-y-8">
            <p class="text-[clamp(1.4rem,2vw,2.7rem)] leading-[1.24] tracking-[-0.012em]"><strong>Grid &amp; interval</strong> - Just as the sun and moon guide the body, rhythm in design and music determines where space appears and where breathing room exists.</p>
            <p class="text-[clamp(1.4rem,2vw,2.7rem)] leading-[1.24] tracking-[-0.012em]"><strong>Composition &amp; hierarchy</strong> - Just as seasons and the yearly cycle coordinate change, rhythm organizes patterns into meaningful structures.</p>
            <p class="text-[clamp(1.4rem,2vw,2.7rem)] leading-[1.24] tracking-[-0.012em]">Rhythm is not only repetition. It is tension and release, action and rest, pattern and variation.</p>
            <p class="text-[clamp(1.4rem,2vw,2.7rem)] leading-[1.24] tracking-[-0.012em]">It is the same principle that makes an interface readable, keeps a melody compelling, and helps a person remain in balance.</p>
            <p class="text-[clamp(1.4rem,2vw,2.7rem)] leading-[1.24] tracking-[-0.012em]">And just as the sun, moon, seasons, and the year shape our physical and emotional rhythms, astrology works with these same cycles. The movements of planets and celestial bodies influence our rhythm, our energy, and our choices: a deeper layer of everything we feel and create.</p>
            <p class="mt-8"><a href="/astrology/" class="line-reveal-inline pb-1 text-[clamp(1.9rem,2.2vw,2.8rem)] tracking-[-0.018em]"><span class="material-symbols-outlined" style="font-size:1em;position:relative;top:0.15em;">east</span> Explore astrology</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
